      "repair_reason": "- [P1] Needs human loader/security-boundary review; no new fix PR should be queued while this candidate PR and canonical issue remain open.; Needs attention: The diff weakens plugin-root containment for loader entry paths without proving the escaped target is a narrow active-host SDK alias.; Review finding: [P1] Keep SDK resolution out of entry containment — src/plugins/loader.ts:2461-2467 - [P1] Require a trusted S... (sha=a2ad4f5887ed9a18a6e7053691b5560afcf4b53b)",
      "review_summary": "This PR modifies `src/plugins/loader.ts` to allow plugin-root boundary failures when the escaped realpath appears to be inside a package named `openclaw`, at runtime, setup-runtime, and CLI metadata load sites.\n\nPR surface: Source +38. Total +38 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. from source, but not from a live packaged run in this review. Current main and `v2026.6.10` keep the strict plugin-root rejection, strict runtime loading can throw, and the Codex plugin imports OpenClaw SDK subpaths through the documented host peer link shape.",
      "review_followup": "- [P1] Needs human loader/security-boundary review; no new fix PR should be queued while this candidate PR and canonical issue remain open.",
