      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): allow host openclaw SDK symlinks that escape plugin root",
        "body": "Closes #93886\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nPlugins that resolve their openclaw peer dependency via an escaping symlink to the host openclaw installation (e.g. codex's `node_modules/openclaw → /app`) were rejected by the boundary check, causing `PluginLoadFailureError` and aborting sub-agent runs.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdded `safeRealpathSync` and `isHostOpenClawPackage` helpers. At all 3 boundary check sites, symlinks that resolve to the host openclaw package are allowed; all other boundary violations are still rejected.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e '...'\n\nsafeRealpathSync + isHostOpenClawPackage test:\nHost openclaw symlink:   true  (ALLOWED)\nExternal package path:   false (BLOCKED)\n``\"\n\nNon-host escaping paths remain rejected. Only host openclaw symlinks bypass the boundary check.",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93886-openclaw-codex-2026-6-8-fails-strict-pl",
        "head_sha": "a2ad4f5887ed9a18a6e7053691b5560afcf4b53b",
